What is a server?
A server is like a powerful computer that stores and provides data and services to other computers (clients) over a network.
Example: When you log into a website, the server processes your login request and retrieves your account information.

What is the role of the domain name?
The role of a domain name is to provide a human-readable address for a website 

What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com

What is the role of the web server
A web server is like a waiter in a restaurant. When you request a webpage, the web server fetches the content and serves it to you.
Example: You request a webpage by typing a URL. The web server processes this request and sends back the HTML page to your browser.

What is the role of the application server?
Process the logic of web application.

What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com
A record (Address record) or a CNAME record (Canonical Name record).

What is the role of the database
Store and manage data.


ou must be able to explain what the issues are with this infrastructure:
SPOF: 
- Web Server: If the web server fails, the entire website becomes unavailable. 
- There is no backup or redundancy shown, meaning the web server is a SPOF.
- Database (MySQL): If the MySQL database server fails, any part of the application that depends on the database will stop functioning.

Cannot scale if too much incoming traffic: 
There is No load Balancer and no backup server to distribute traffic.